imilarly, the mystic \u003cem\u003eyogī\u003c/em\u003e who practices the \u003cem\u003eyoga\u003c/em\u003e system with half-open eyes, ceasing all material activities, desires some satisfaction for his personal self. But a person acting in Kṛṣṇa consciousness works for the satisfaction of the whole, without self-interest. A Kṛṣṇa conscious person has no desire for self-satisfaction. His criterion of success is the satisfaction of Kṛṣṇa, and thus he is the perfect \u003cem\u003esannyāsī,\u003c/em\u003e or perfect \u003cem\u003eyogī.\u003c/em\u003e Lord Caitanya, the highest perfectional symbol of renunciation, prays in this way:\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"verse_text\",\"id\":1760,\"bb\":1558,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/6/1/b1558/\",\"body_value\":\"\u003cem\u003ena dhanaṁ na janaṁ na sundarīṁ\u003cbr /\u003ekavitāṁ vā jagad-īśa kāmaye\u003cbr /\u003emama janmani janmanīśvare\u003cbr /\u003ebhavatād bhaktir ahaitukī tvayi\u003c/em\u003e\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":1761,\"bb\":1559,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/6/1/b1559/\",\"body_value\":\"“O Almighty Lord, I have no desire to accumulate wealth, nor to enjoy beautiful women. Nor do I want any number of followers. What I want only is the causeless mercy of Your devotional service in my life, birth after birth.”\"}]}],\"short_title\":\"Bg. 6.1\",\"medium_title\":\"Bhagavad-gītā As It Is 6.1\"},{\"id\":1762,\"meta\":{\"type\":\"books.Verse\",\"slug\":\"2\",\"show_in_menus\":false,\"seo_title\":\"\",\"search_description\":\"\",\"first_published_at\":null,\"alias_of\":null,\"locale\":\"en\"},\"title\":\"TEXT 2\",\"advanced_view_url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/6/advanced-view/#bb1560\",\"language_menu\":[{\"display_name\":\"አማርኛ (Ethiopian)\",\"language_code\":\"am\",\"enabled\":false,\"url_path\":\"/am/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Български (Bulgarian)\",\"language_code\":\"bg\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/bg/library/bg/6/2/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Čeština (Czech)\",\"langua