 the world, and he is the dearest servitor of the Lord. \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"7\",{\"children\":\"Na ca tasmān manuṣyeṣu kaścin me priya-kṛttamaḥ\"}],\" (\",[\"$\",\"$L29\",\"9\",{\"href\":\"/en/library/bg/18/69/\",\"children\":\"Bg. 18.69\"}],\"). In other words, a devotee of the Lord always looks to the welfare of all living entities, and in this way he is factually the friend of everyone. He is the best \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"11\",{\"children\":\"yogī\"}],\" because he does not desire perfection in \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"13\",{\"children\":\"yoga\"}],\" for his personal benefit, but tries for others also. He does not envy his fellow living entities. Here is a contrast between a pure devotee of the Lord and a \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"15\",{\"children\":\"yogī\"}],\" interested only in his personal elevation. The \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"17\",{\"children\":\"yogī\"}],\" who has withdrawn to a secluded place in order to meditate perfectly may not be as perfect as a devotee who is trying his best to turn every man toward Kṛṣṇa consciousness.\"]}]}]]]}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"d1:[\"$\",\"div\",\"1968-devanagari,1968-devanagari\",{\"className\":\"av-devanagari\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center em:leading-5 em:text-xl font-bold em:mb-4 hidden\",\"children\":\"Devanagari\"}],[[\"$\",\"$L4a\",\"child-1969\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:27:child_items:0:children:0\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-lg text-center\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"अर्जुन उवाच\u003cbr/\u003eयोऽयं योगस्त्वया प्रोक्त: साम्येन मधुसूदन ।\u003cbr/\u003eएतस्याहं न पश्यामि चञ्चलत्वात्स्थितिं स्थिराम् ॥ ३३ ॥\"}}]}]]]}]\nd2:[\"$\",\"div\",\"1968-verse_text,1968-verse_text\",{\"className\":\"av-verse_text\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center em:leading-5 em:text-xl font-bold em:mb-4 hidden\",\"children\":\"Verse text\"}],[[\